Max R. READ, Appellant, v. PACIFIC COAST BREEDERS’ ASSOCIATION et al., Appellees. No. 6948. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 13, 1933. Miller & Boyken, Carroll A. Gordon, and Joseph E. Connolly, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Edwin Y. McKenzie and John J. Taaffe, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRE CHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

After submission of the cause, counsel present stipulation for dismissal of the appeal, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal dismissed, without costs to either party.
